What is Java?
----------------
Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language developed to create portable, secure, and robust applications.


Why Java is High-Level?
------------------------------
1. Easy-to-read syntax
2. No direct memory manipulation
3. Automatic garbage collection
4. Hardware independent

 Why Java is Object-Oriented?
 ------------------------------------
1. Uses classes and objects
2. Supports all OOP principles
3. Models real-world problems

Evolution of Java
